aa(lp85
VBut the goals of interplanetary exploration and planetary preservation
p86
aVare not opposed to one another.
p87
aVNo, they're in fact two sides of the same goal:
p88
aVto understand, preserve and improve life into the future.
p89
aVThe extreme environments of our own world are alien vistas.
p90
aVThey're just closer to home.
p91
aVIf we can understand how to create and maintain habitable spaces
p92
aVout of hostile, inhospitable spaces here on Earth,
p93
aVperhaps we can meet the needs of both preserving our own environment
p94
aVand moving beyond it.
